reviews.text: Quite an average Starbucks. Coffee was OK. Staff were really friendly. There were lots of seats inside, the air conditioning was nice and cold, and the bathroom was clean. We really wish there was a baby changing table though!
Very average staff attitude on sundays. Orders are taken wrongly. Much more to be improved.

A good get-together place for business partners or friends. Here you can relax for a nice cup of coffee or fruit juices, for a bite to eat e.g. quiche, sandwiches or pies. For me as a health conscious person, I had yoghurt with crunchy granolas.
Not very large. Can cater about 50 people. Good for nearby offices.
Usually....a very good coffee
